               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Za-Mikāʾel ʾAragāwi "Vita of Za-Mikāʾel ʾAragāwi" (fols. 5ra-35rb l.9)&#xD;
II) Taʾāmra Za-Mikāʾel ʾAragāwi "Miracles of Za-Mikāʾel ʾAragāwi" (fols. 35rb l.10-46vb)&#xD;
- Introductory homily (fols. 35rb l.10-36vb l.13)&#xD;
- 5 miracles (fols. 36vb l.14-46vb)&#xD;
III) Malkǝʾa Za-Mikāʾel ʾAragāwi "Image of Za-Mikāʾel ʾAragāwi" (fols. 47ra-50rb)&#xD;
IV) Gadla Gabra Krǝstos "Vita of Gabra Krǝstos [St Alexius]" (fols. 50ra-75vb)&#xD;
&#xD;
Additio 1.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The explicit of Text I as presented in I. GUIDI, Il "Gadla ʼAragâwi", Roma 1895 (pp. 35-36 starting with the words: ተፈጸመ፡ ገድሉ፡ ወተኣምሪሁ፡ ለብእሴ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ቅዱስ፡ ወብፁዕ፡ አቡነ፡ አረጋዊ...) is missing.</note>
                     <note>For the collection of miracles of Za-Mikāʾel ʾAragāwi see A. BRITA, I Racconti Tradizionali sulla "Seconda Cristianizzazione" dell'Etiopia, il Ciclo Agriografico dei Nove Santi, Napoli 2010, pp. 232-34.</note>
                     <note>Text IV comprises the "List of Saints" (<locus target="#63ra">63ra</locus> l.2-64vb l.20), the "Song of Dāwit" (<locus target="#64vb">64vb</locus> l.20-69va l.7) and the longer version of the kidan-scene (<locus target="#66ra">66ra</locus> l.22-69ra l.4).</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
